  "module": {
    "path": "src/common/structure",
    "name": "structure",
    "purpose": "Owns shared structural utilities for the common crate. channel.rs defines local and TCP-backed remoc channel helpers: accept_channel resolves the bind address and expected token from config, binds the listener once, and accepts in a loop until one connection completes the transport handshake and presents the valid token within a 5-second per-connection timeout, abandoning connections that fail authentication, transport, or the timeout while continuing to accept, and returning early only on server-side setup, bind, or runtime failures; connect_channel resolves the connect address and token from config and makes a single attempt, surfacing ChannelError::Auth when the server rejects the token. It also defines the ChannelEndpoint client/host/telemetry channel-role selector and shared net endpoint wrappers. work_queue.rs defines the generic WorkQueue over working and completed maps, including borrowed access through with and clear() cleanup that empties both maps for host-disconnect session reset. mod.rs is namespace and re-export wiring only.",
    "changeStatus": "modified"
  },
